EURUS COMBINE HILLS I LLC FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF NO. 1
1. Availability. As provided in this Tariff, Eurus Combine Hills I LLC (Seller) makes available electrical energy and capacity available for sale at wholesale.
2. Applicability. This Tariff applies to all wholesale sales of electric electrical energy and capacity from Seller's generation facility that are not made under another tariff or rate schedule that is on file with the Commission.
3. Rates. All sales under this Tariff shall be made at rates that are established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions of salesales under this Tariff shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and seller. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions that the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 6. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 1 seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. ? 35.36(a), in the Northwest. Seller is also a Category 1 seller in the Northeast, Southeast, Central, Southwest Power Pool, and Southwest regions. 7. Limitations and Exemptions. Seller does not have any limitations on its market-based rate authority except as otherwise provided in this Tariff. Seller has been granted waiver of (a) Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations regarding the filing of tariffs, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (b) Part 41 of the Commission's regulations regarding accounts, records, and memoranda; (c) Part 101 of the Commission's regulations regarding uniform system of accounts; and (d) Part 141 of the Commission's regulations regarding statements and reports. Seller has been granted blanket approval under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for future issuances of securities and assumptions of liabilities, subject to objection by an interested party. See Eurus Combine Hills I LLC, Docket No. ER04-135-000 and ER11-2399-000.
8. Effective Date and Duration. This Tariff is effective upon the date that is authorized by the Commission. This Tariff shall continue in effect until terminated or changed in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements. 9. Modification. Seller may unilaterally apply under section 205 of the Federal Power Act for modification of this Tariff.
